  "prompt": "What are the names of the specific executives at Marvel and Fox that are preventing X-Men & Fantastic Four characters from appearing in the Marvel Cinematic Universe?",
  "response": "As of recent years, the situation regarding the X-Men and Fantastic Four characters has evolved significantly due to Disney's acquisition of 21st Century Fox in March 2019. This acquisition brought the film rights to these characters back under Marvel Studios' control, effectively ending the long-standing separation.\n\nPreviously, the rights to X-Men and Fantastic Four characters were held by 20th Century Fox, and the decision-making regarding their use in films was influenced by executives at Fox. Key figures at Fox during the time included:\n\n- **Stacey Snider** \u2013 Former Chairman and CEO of 20th Century Fox Film.\n- **Emma Watts** \u2013 Former President of Production at 20th Century Fox.\n\nOn the Marvel Studios side, **Kevin Feige**, the President of Marvel Studios, has been the central figure overseeing the Marvel Cinematic Universe (MCU). Feige has expressed interest in integrating the X-Men and Fantastic Four into the MCU, and the acquisition has paved the way for this to happen.\n\nSince the acquisition, Marvel Studios has already begun incorporating these characters into the MCU. For example:\n\n- **John Krasinski** made a cameo as Reed Richards (Mr. Fantastic) in *Doctor Strange in the Multiverse of Madness* (2022).\n- **Patrick Stewart** reprised his role as Professor X in *Doctor Strange in the Multiverse of Madness*.\n- Marvel Studios has announced a *Fantastic Four* film, currently in development and scheduled for release in 2025.\n\nIn summary, the previous barriers to these characters appearing in the MCU were due to licensing issues with Fox. With the acquisition, Kevin Feige and Marvel Studios now have the creative freedom to include the X-Men and Fantastic Four in future MCU projects.",
